<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>Attalos Andron son of Peritas the son of Demetrius dedicated this column with its capital for his homeland at his own expense.</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>One of the column base dedications from west portico of the East Court of the Hadrianic Baths. From north section: <xref type="inscription" n="1114" href="050206">5.206</xref> (MiItal 8 i and ii), <xref type="inscription" n="1116" href="050201">5.201</xref> (=Haussoullier1), <xref type="iAph">1119</xref> (=Boulanger A 73, no.11); from the south section <xref type="iAph">1115</xref> (=Boulanger B, 21 no.28), ?<xref type="inscription" n="1117" href="050202">5.202</xref> (=Museum 154), ?<xref type="iAph">1120</xref> (=Museum 158); cf also <xref type="iAph">1118</xref> (=68.272)</p>
</div>
